      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FEHMARN (1) was big odds on debut here but did much better than the betting would've suggested, beaten under a length in the small field in an encouraging effort. Have to take that on face value and this doesn't look a particularly deep maiden. BLITZ AIR (3) struggled in the heavy ground at Warrnambool first up but was kept safe in betting there and did run well on debut in a hot maiden here last time in. She can improve sharply. PENINSULA ROSE (8) was just fair fresh at Mornington when racing keenly, she should have taken the edge off and can give a sight. THROME THE MONEY (9) is a filly by Thronum on debut for the Verwey-Mitchell yard who has won a jumpout leading in and could show up. TICKETY BOO (10) is a Dirty Work filly for the Colin Scott yard who wouldn't shock.",
